      },
      {
        "type": "infoPanel",
        "attrs": {
          "tone": "info",
          "title": "Also",
          "body": "1/2 cup (100 g) peppermint chips Andes; 2 tbsp crushed candy canes for topping, optional."
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Method"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "orderedList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Preheat oven to 350 degrees and line two baking sheets with parchment paper."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Add softened, unsalted butter, light brown sugar, and granulated sugar to a large bowl. Cream the butter and sugars with an electric mixer for two minutes, or until light and fluffy."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "To the creamed butter and sugars add the egg yolks, peppermint extract and vanilla. Mix on medium speed for two minutes, or until the mixture is pale in color and fluffy."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Add in the flour, cocoa powder, baking powder, baking soda and salt and mix until combined."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "(Please see recipe notes on properly measuring the flour for these cookies. Too much flour will ruin the cookies consistency.)"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Add in the peppermint chips and chocolate chips and mix just until incorporated."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Scoop the dough into 18 balls and arrange them two inches apart on the prepared baking sheets."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Bake the cookies for 10-12 minutes. (10 for chewier centers, 12 for crispier edges.)"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "After baking, let the cookies cool on the baking sheets for two minutes, then transfer them to a cooling rack to cool for 10 minutes. Sprinkle crushed candy canes over the cookies if you wish and then serve!"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Store left overs in an airtight container for up to three days."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "troubleshooter",
        "attrs": {
          "heading": "If something goes wrong",
          "intro": "A few of the more common issues, and what tends to fix them.",
          "items": [
            {
              "symptom": "Cookies spread too thin and crisp",
              "cause": "Butter too soft, or oven not hot enough.",
              "fix": "Chill the dough for 30 minutes before baking. Preheat the oven properly — 180°C means 180°C on an oven thermometer, not the dial."
            },
            {
              "symptom": "Cookies came out cakey, not chewy",
              "cause": "Over-mixed once the flour went in, or too much flour.",
              "fix": "Stop mixing as soon as the flour disappears. For chewier cookies, replace some plain flour with bread flour for more gluten."
            },
            {
              "symptom": "Cookies stuck to the tray",
              "cause": "Tried to lift before they'd set.",
              "fix": "Leave them on the tray for five minutes after baking — they're too soft to move when hot. Lift onto a rack with a palette knife."
            },
            {
              "symptom": "Burnt bottoms, raw middles",
              "cause": "Tray too thin, or rack too low.",
              "fix": "Use a heavier baking tray, line with baking paper, and bake on the middle shelf."
            }
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Variations"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Add-ins: 75 g dark chocolate chips, chopped walnuts, dried cranberries, or a pinch of sea salt on top before baking."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Gluten-free: replace plain flour with a 1-to-1 gluten-free blend that includes xanthan gum."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Make ahead, freezing, leftovers"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Best fresh. Leftovers keep two days in the fridge; reheat covered with a splash of liquid."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Where this dish lives"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "A classic American home recipe — generous, comforting, made for a crowd. The proportions are heartier than the British equivalent; the method is built for a Sunday afternoon."
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  }
